{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017wM9N8YQcK6b5m7heXykQB","type":"tool_result","content":"4400\t    `cancelled` (1 test).\n4401\t  - `dogpileCancelMutation definition`: pins `actionId` and\n4402\t    `resourceType` so audit-row contract regressions break a test\n4403\t    rather than ship silently (1 test).\n4404\t  - `dogpile.cancel via runPeekMutation` (9 tests):\n4405\t    - **Scheduled + future starts_at success** — emits\n4406\t      `peek.change.applied` with `[{ field: \"status\", before:\n4407\t      \"scheduled\", after: \"cancelled\" }]`, transaction begins exactly\n4408\t      once, rolls back never, SELECT precedes UPDATE, UPDATE binds the\n4409\t      `eventId` and includes the `status = 'cancelled'` literal, audit\n4410\t      payload's `requestId` + `actorEmail` + `route` round-trip, and\n4411\t      audit is written on the in-tx Sql so the change + audit row are\n4412\t      atomic.\n4413\t    - **active denial** — `peek.change.rejected` with\n4414\t      `execution_failed: invalid_status: active`, transaction rolls\n4415\t      back, no UPDATE issued, `payload.changes === null`.\n4416\t    - **ended denial** — same shape with `invalid_status: ended`.\n4417\t    - **cancelled (no-op) denial** — same shape with\n4418\t      `invalid_status: cancelled`, asserting that re-cancelling an\n4419\t      already-cancelled row is rejected because FR-14 audit rows must\n4420\t      reflect a real movement.\n4421\t    - **starts_at in past** — scheduled in DB but `starts_at <= now()`\n4422\t      → `execution_failed: starts_at_in_past`. Documents the worker\n4423\t      promotion-from-scheduled race so admins cannot win it from the\n4424\t      admin UI.\n4425\t    - **Unknown event** — empty SELECT result returns\n4426\t      `execution_failed: unknown_event: <id>`; transaction still\n4427\t      begins (and rolls back) so the SELECT-not-found path is covered\n4428\t      end-to-end.\n4429\t    - **Non-admin actor (business)** — runner short-circuits before\n4430\t      `sql.begin`; `peek.change.rejected` with `rejectionReason:\n4431\t      \"unauthorized\"` and zero SQL calls.\n4432\t    - **Null actor role** — same denial path; `rejectionReason:\n4433\t      \"unauthorized\"`.\n4434\t    - **Schema rejection** — non-numeric `eventId=\"abc\"` returns\n4435\t      `invalid_input` with `fieldErrors.eventId`; no transaction\n4436\t      opened; audit row carries `rejectionReason: \"invalid_input\"`\n4437\t      and `payload.changes === null`.\n4438\t\n4439\t- **Test scaffolding parity with `kol-rate.test.ts` /\n4440\t  `fraud-flag.test.ts`**:\n4441\t  - `createAuditWriter()` records `eventType` + `payload` + which\n4442\t    `Sql` was used.\n4443\t  - `createSqlMock()` emulates `sql.begin` and the tagged-template\n4444\t    invocation pattern, returning the `existingRow` for SELECTs\n4445\t    (shaped as `{id, status, startsInFuture}` to match\n4446\t    `dogpile.ts:fetchExistingRow`) and optionally rejecting UPDATEs\n4447\t    via `failOnUpdate` (parallel to fraud-flag's `failOnUpdate`).\n4448\t  - `REGISTRY` is a frozen single-entry registry holding only\n4449\t    `dogpileCancelMutation` so the runner test path doesn't pull in\n4450\t    unrelated production mutations.\n4451\t\n4452\t- **Targeted checks** (CLAUDE.md TS rule):\n4453\t  - `cd peek && pnpm lint` ✅\n4454\t  - `cd peek && pnpm typecheck` ✅\n4455\t  - `cd peek && pnpm test --run` ✅ (82 files, 936/936 — +17 new\n4456\t    tests, no regressions; full suite green).\n4457\t\n4458\t- **Next**: `[engine] Selected reward_config edit mutation with key\n4459\t  allowlist, value validation, explicit confirmation flag, and\n4460\t  before/after audit.`\n4461\t\n4462\t## Iteration 151 — 2026-04-26 — Reward config edit mutation\n4463\t\n4464\t- **Item**: `[engine] Selected reward_config edit mutation with key\n4465\t  allowlist, value validation, explicit confirmation flag, and\n4466\t  before/after audit.`\n4467\t\n4468\t- **Files added** (1):\n4469\t  - `peek/src/server/mutations/reward-config.ts` — FR-14 mutation for\n4470\t    `reward_config.update` (admin-only).\n4471\t\n4472\t- **Files modified** (2):\n4473\t  - `peek/src/server/mutations/registry.ts` — register\n4474\t    `rewardConfigUpdateMutation` alongside KOL rate / fraud flag /\n4475\t    dogpile.\n4476\t  - `peek/src/server/mutations/index.ts` — export the new mutation,\n4477\t    schema, allowlist, and value-validation helper.\n4478\t\n4479\t- **Design choices**:\n4480\t  - **Key allowlist**: `PEEK_REWARD_CONFIG_EDITABLE_KEYS` is derived\n4481\t    from `PEEK_REWARD_CONFIG_KEY_REGISTRY` (filtering out\n4482\t    `expectedType === \"unknown\"`). Single source of truth so the admin\n4483\t    UI dropdown, the schema, and the runtime guard cannot drift.\n4484\t  - **Value validation by expected type**: integer (`^-?[0-9]+$`),\n4485\t    lamports (`^[0-9]+$`), float (Number.isFinite + must contain a\n4486\t    decimal so operators don't slip an integer into a float slot),\n4487\t    ratio (Number.isFinite ∈ [0,1]). Validation runs in a zod\n4488\t    `superRefine` so failures land on the runner's `invalid_input`\n4489\t    path with the expected `fieldErrors.value` shape.\n4490\t  - **Explicit confirmation**: `confirm: z.literal(true)` — missing or\n4491\t    `false` is rejected before any DB work, matching the FR-14\n4492\t    \"explicit confirmation and clear display of old/new values\"\n4493\t    requirement on the engine side. The frontend wiring (separate\n4494\t    iteration) renders the old/new pair before submission.\n4495\t  - **No-op rejection**: if the new `value` already matches the row,\n4496\t    `execute` throws `noop_value` so the audit row reflects a real\n4497\t    movement (parity with the dogpile-cancel \"real movement\" rule).\n4498\t  - **Audit diff**: single `[{ field: \"value\", before, after }]`.\n4499\t    `updated_at` is bumped server-side and stays out of the diff\n4500\t    (matches the kol-rate `updated_at` precedent).\n4501\t\n4502\t- **Failure semantics** (surfaced through the runner's execute path):\n4503\t  - Disallowed key / malformed value / missing confirmation → schema\n4504\t    `invalid_input` before any DB work; `peek.change.rejected` with\n4505\t    `rejectionReason: \"invalid_input\"`.\n4506\t  - Allowlisted key missing in DB → `execution_failed: unknown_key:\n4507\t    <key>` (only if a registered key was never seeded).\n4508\t  - No-op (value unchanged) → `execution_failed: noop_value`.\n4509\t  - Non-admin actor → runner short-circuits with\n4510\t    `peek.change.rejected` and `rejectionReason: \"unauthorized\"`.\n4511\t\n4512\t- **Authorization**: `reward_config.update` is admin-only per\n4513\t  `PEEK_ACTION_RULES` already declared in\n4514\t  `peek/src/server/access-policy.ts:158`. The runner enforces this\n4515\t  before `execute` is called.\n4516\t\n4517\t- **Targeted checks** (CLAUDE.md TS rule):\n4518\t  - `cd peek && pnpm lint` ✅\n4519\t  - `cd peek && pnpm typecheck` ✅\n4520\t  - `cd peek && pnpm test --run` ✅ (82 files, 936/936 — no\n4521\t    regressions; dedicated mutation tests land in the next iteration\n4522\t    \"[test] Reward config mutation tests\").\n4523\t\n4524\t- **Next**: `[test] Reward config mutation tests: allowed key success,\n4525\t  disallowed key denial, invalid value, missing confirmation,\n4526\t  unauthorized actor, audit payload.`\n4527\t## Iteration 151 — 2026-04-26 — OK\n4528\t## Iteration 150 — 2026-04-26T19:18:20Z — OK\n4529\t- **Log**: iteration-150.log\n4530\t\n4531\t\n4532\t## Iteration 151 — 2026-04-26 — Reward config mutation tests\n4533\t\n4534\t- **Item**: `[test] Reward config mutation tests: allowed key success,\n4535\t  disallowed key denial, invalid value, missing confirmation,\n4536\t  unauthorized actor, audit payload.`\n4537\t\n4538\t- **Files added** (1):\n4539\t  - `peek/src/server/mutations/__tests__/reward-config.test.ts` — 32\n4540\t    unit tests across allowlist derivation, value validator, schema,\n4541\t    definition wiring, and full runner-orchestrated FR-14 path for\n4542\t    `reward_config.update`.\n4543\t\n4544\t- **Test groups**:\n4545\t  - `PEEK_REWARD_CONFIG_EDITABLE_KEYS` (2 tests): every editable key\n4546\t    is registered with a non-`unknown` expected type; the seed list\n4547\t    includes `points_per_dollar`, `reward_pool_fee_share`, and\n4548\t    `sol_crate_min_value`.\n4549\t  - `validateRewardConfigValueForKey` (9 tests): integer happy/sad,\n4550\t    lamports happy / negative / non-numeric, float (decimal accepted,\n4551\t    pure-integer rejected as `expected_float_with_decimal`,\n4552\t    non-finite rejected), ratio in-range / out-of-range, unknown key\n4553\t    short-circuits.\n4554\t  - `rewardConfigUpdateInputSchema` (8 tests): valid shape, trim,\n4555\t    disallowed key reject, malformed value reject (with field error\n4556\t    on `value`), missing `confirm` reject, `confirm: false` reject,\n4557\t    empty value after trim reject, strict extra-fields reject.\n4558\t  - `rewardConfigUpdateMutation definition` (1 test): pins\n4559\t    `actionId=\"reward_config.update\"` and\n4560\t    `resourceType=\"reward_config\"` so audit-row contract regressions\n4561\t    fail a test rather than ship silently.\n4562\t  - `reward_config.update via runPeekMutation` (12 tests):\n4563\t    - **Allowed integer key success** — emits\n4564\t      `peek.change.applied` with `[{ field: \"value\", before: \"100\",\n4565\t      after: \"200\" }]`, transaction begins exactly once, never rolls\n4566\t      back, SELECT precedes UPDATE, UPDATE binds\n4567\t      `[\"200\", \"points_per_dollar\"]` and includes\n4568\t      `update reward_config` + `updated_at = now()` in the SQL,\n4569\t      audit's `requestId` + `actorEmail` + `route` round-trip, and\n4570\t      audit is written on the in-tx Sql so the change + audit row are\n4571\t      atomic.\n4572\t    - **Allowed ratio key success** — applied audit emitted with the\n4573\t      0.1 → 0.25 diff for `reward_pool_fee_share`.\n4574\t    - **Disallowed key** — schema-layer reject;\n4575\t      `peek.change.rejected` with `rejectionReason: \"invalid_input\"`,\n4576\t      `fieldErrors.key` populated, transaction never opened.\n4577\t    - **Malformed integer value (1.5)** — schema-layer reject;\n4578\t      `fieldErrors.value` populated, transaction never opened.\n4579\t    - **Out-of-range ratio (1.5)** — schema-layer reject via\n4580\t      `superRefine`; `fieldErrors.value` populated, transaction\n4581\t      never opened.\n4582\t    - **Missing confirm** — schema-layer reject;\n4583\t      `fieldErrors.confirm` populated, transaction never opened.\n4584\t    - **Confirm: false** — schema-layer reject; transaction never\n4585\t      opened.\n4586\t    - **No-op (value unchanged)** — `execution_failed: noop_value`;\n4587\t      transaction begins once + rolls back, SELECT runs, UPDATE\n4588\t      never runs, `payload.changes === null`.\n4589\t    - **Allowlisted key missing in DB** —\n4590\t      `execution_failed: unknown_key: points_per_dollar`; transaction\n4591\t      begins + rolls back, SELECT runs, UPDATE never runs.\n4592\t    - **Non-admin (business) actor** — runner short-circuits before\n4593\t      `sql.begin`; `peek.change.rejected` with `rejectionReason:\n4594\t      \"unauthorized\"` and zero SQL calls.\n4595\t    - **Null actor role** — same denial path; `rejectionReason:\n4596\t      \"unauthorized\"`.\n4597\t\n4598\t- **Test scaffolding parity with `kol-rate.test.ts` /\n4599\t  `fraud-flag.test.ts` / `dogpile.test.ts`**:\n4600\t  - `createAuditWriter()` records `eventType` + `payload` + which\n4601\t    `Sql` was used.\n4602\t  - `createSqlMock()` emulates `sql.begin` and the tagged-template\n4603\t    invocation pattern, returning the `existingRow` for SELECTs\n4604\t    (shaped as `{key, value}` to match\n4605\t    `reward-config.ts:fetchExistingRow`) and optionally rejecting\n4606\t    UPDATEs via `failOnUpdate`.\n4607\t  - `RE