{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0118HZ36hGdk6UPawnVL2e24","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t// Reward config table for /economy/rewards (FR-9).\n2\t//\n3\t// Read-only dense table over `PeekRewardConfigRow`. Each row shows the key,\n4\t// value, expected value type chip, an inline definition (or an \"unknown key\"\n5\t// hint for rows whose key has not been registered), and the last-updated\n6\t// timestamp. Editing is out of scope for this iteration (FR-14 / future\n7\t// reward-config mutation work owns that flow).\n8\timport type { CSSProperties } from \"react\";\n9\timport type {\n10\t  PeekRewardConfigExpectedType,\n11\t  PeekRewardConfigRow,\n12\t  PeekStatusTone,\n13\t} from \"../lib/types/peek\";\n14\timport { StatusChip } from \"./status-chip\";\n15\t\n16\texport type RewardConfigTableProps = {\n17\t  rows: ReadonlyArray<PeekRewardConfigRow>;\n18\t  error?: string | null;\n19\t};\n20\t\n21\tconst TYPE_TONE: Record<PeekRewardConfigExpectedType, PeekStatusTone> = {\n22\t  integer: \"info\",\n23\t  float: \"info\",\n24\t  ratio: \"info\",\n25\t  lamports: \"info\",\n26\t  unknown: \"warning\",\n27\t};\n28\t\n29\texport function RewardConfigTable({\n30\t  rows,\n31\t  error = null,\n32\t}: RewardConfigTableProps) {\n33\t  if (error) {\n34\t    return (\n35\t      <div role=\"alert\" style={errorStyle}>\n36\t        Reward config unavailable: {error}\n37\t      </div>\n38\t    );\n39\t  }\n40\t\n41\t  if (rows.length === 0) {\n42\t    return (\n43\t      <div role=\"status\" style={emptyStyle}>\n44\t        <p style={emptyTitleStyle}>No reward_config rows.</p>\n45\t        <p style={emptyBodyStyle}>\n46\t          The `reward_config` table has not been seeded yet, so no economy\n47\t          parameters can be displayed.\n48\t        </p>\n49\t      </div>\n50\t    );\n51\t  }\n52\t\n53\t  return (\n54\t    <div style={wrapperStyle}>\n55\t      <table style={tableStyle}>\n56\t        <thead>\n57\t          <tr style={headerRowStyle}>\n58\t            <th style={headerCellStyle(\"left\")}>Key</th>\n59\t            <th style={headerCellStyle(\"left\")}>Type</th>\n60\t            <th style={headerCellStyle(\"right\")}>Value</th>\n61\t            <th style={headerCellStyle(\"left\")}>Definition</th>\n62\t            <th style={headerCellStyle(\"left\")}>Updated</th>\n63\t          </tr>\n64\t        </thead>\n65\t        <tbody>\n66\t          {rows.map((row) => (\n67\t            <tr key={row.key} style={bodyRowStyle}>\n68\t              <td style={{ ...bodyCellStyle(\"left\"), fontFamily: \"monospace\" }}>\n69\t                {row.key}\n70\t              </td>\n71\t              <td style={bodyCellStyle(\"left\")}>\n72\t                <StatusChip\n73\t                  label={row.expectedType}\n74\t                  tone={TYPE_TONE[row.expectedType]}\n75\t                />\n76\t              </td>\n77\t              <td style={{ ...bodyCellStyle(\"right\"), fontFamily: \"monospace\" }}>\n78\t                {row.value}\n79\t              </td>\n80\t              <td style={bodyCellStyle(\"left\")}>\n81\t                {row.definition ?? (\n82\t                  <span style={unknownStyle}>\n83\t                    Unregistered key — extend\n84\t                    PEEK_REWARD_CONFIG_KEY_REGISTRY to document this.\n85\t                  </span>\n86\t                )}\n87\t              </td>\n88\t              <td style={bodyCellStyle(\"left\")}>{row.updatedAt}</td>\n89\t            </tr>\n90\t          ))}\n91\t        </tbody>\n92\t      </table>\n93\t    </div>\n94\t  );\n95\t}\n96\t\n97\tconst wrapperStyle: CSSProperties = {\n98\t  overflowX: \"auto\",\n99\t  border: \"1px solid #1e293b\",\n100\t  borderRadius: \"0.75rem\",\n101\t};\n102\t\n103\tconst tableStyle: CSSProperties = {\n104\t  width: \"100%\",\n105\t  borderCollapse: \"collapse\",\n106\t};\n107\t\n108\tconst headerRowStyle: CSSProperties = {\n109\t  background: \"#111827\",\n110\t  color: \"#94a3b8\",\n111\t};\n112\t\n113\tconst bodyRowStyle: CSSProperties = {\n114\t  borderTop: \"1px solid #1e293b\",\n115\t};\n116\t\n117\tconst unknownStyle: CSSProperties = {\n118\t  color: \"#fde68a\",\n119\t  fontSize: \"0.8125rem\",\n120\t};\n121\t\n122\tfunction headerCellStyle(align: \"left\" | \"right\" | \"center\"): CSSProperties {\n123\t  return {\n124\t    padding: \"0.75rem\",\n125\t    textAlign: align,\n126\t    fontSize: \"0.875rem\",\n127\t    fontWeight: 600,\n128\t  };\n129\t}\n130\t\n131\tfunction bodyCellStyle(align: \"left\" | \"right\" | \"center\"): CSSProperties {\n132\t  return {\n133\t    padding: \"0.75rem\",\n134\t    textAlign: align,\n135\t    fontSize: \"0.875rem\",\n136\t    color: \"#e2e8f0\",\n137\t    verticalAlign: \"top\",\n138\t  };\n139\t}\n140\t\n141\tconst errorStyle: CSSProperties = {\n142\t  margin: 0,\n143\t  padding: \"0.75rem 1rem\",\n144\t  borderRadius: \"0.75rem\",\n145\t  background: \"#3f1d1d\",\n146\t  color: \"#fecaca\",\n147\t};\n148\t\n149\tconst emptyStyle: CSSProperties = {\n150\t  padding: \"1.5rem\",\n151\t  borderRadius: \"0.75rem\",\n152\t  border: \"1px dashed #334155\",\n153\t  background: \"#0b1220\",\n154\t  color: \"#cbd5f5\",\n155\t  display: \"grid\",\n156\t  gap: \"0.5rem\",\n157\t};\n158\t\n159\tconst emptyTitleStyle: CSSProperties = {\n160\t  margin: 0,\n161\t  fontSize: \"1rem\",\n162\t  fontWeight: 600,\n163\t};\n164\t\n165\tconst emptyBodyStyle: CSSProperties = {\n166\t  margin: 0,\n167\t  fontSize: \"0.875rem\",\n168\t  color: \"#94a3b8\",\n169\t};\n170\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01GwpxxCj3UiMN4YiDjfsvUM","session_id":"3fc3c40b-0944-44dd-9202-74a9cef80e25","uuid":"cd9c92c4-