{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GwpxxCj3UiMN4YiDjfsvUM","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent. Now I have enough information. Let me compile the findings:\n\n## Exploration Report: FR-14 Mutation UI Wiring for Peek Admin\n\n### 1. Four Mutation Pages & Existing Gating\n\n**Page 1: KOL Rate Update**\n- **File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/app/growth/kol/page.tsx`\n- **Access gate**: `getPeekActorContext()` + `isRouteAllowedForRole(ROUTE, actor?.role)` (lines 18-19)\n- **Route**: `/growth/kol` (line 15)\n- **Table component**: `GrowthKolTable` (line 80)\n- **Form plumbing**: None yet; table is read-only, no action buttons\n\n**Page 2: Dogpile Cancel**\n- **File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/app/operations/dogpile/page.tsx`\n- **Access gate**: `getPeekActorContext()` + `isRouteAllowedForRole(ROUTE, actor?.role)` (lines 55-56)\n- **Route**: `/operations/dogpile` (line 48)\n- **Table component**: `DogpileEventsTable` (line 147)\n- **Form plumbing**: None yet; table is read-only. Page comment (lines 13-16) notes FR-14 `dogpile.cancel` action id is not yet implemented\n\n**Page 3: Reward Config Update**\n- **File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/app/economy/rewards/page.tsx`\n- **Access gate**: `getPeekActorContext()` + `isRouteAllowedForRole(ROUTE, actor?.role)` (lines 42-43)\n- **Route**: `/economy/rewards` (line 39)\n- **Table component**: `RewardConfigTable` (line 149)\n- **Form plumbing**: None yet; table is read-only. Page comment (lines 6-13) notes editing is out of scope for current iteration; FR-14 will wire it\n\n**Page 4: Fraud Flag Status Update**\n- **File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/app/operations/dogpile/page.tsx` (same page as dogpile, section 2)\n- **Access gate**: Same as dogpile page (lines 55-56)\n- **Route**: `/operations/dogpile` (rendered within the same route)\n- **Table component**: `FraudFlagsTable` (line 165)\n- **Form plumbing**: None yet; table is read-only. Page comment (lines 14-16) notes FR-14 `fraud_flag.status.update` action id is not yet implemented\n\n### 2. Existing Mutation Test Coverage\n\nTests exist for all four mutations + runner orchestration:\n- `fraud-flag.test.ts`\n- `kol-rate.test.ts`\n- `dogpile.test.ts`\n- `reward-config.test.ts`\n- `runner.test.ts`\n\nNo duplicates to avoid.\n\n### 3. Table Component Signatures & Rendering\n\n**GrowthKolTable**\n- **Props**: `{ rows: ReadonlyArray<PeekKolPerformanceRow>; error?: string | null }`\n- **Columns**: User, Wallet, Rate (bps), Set by, Created, Updated, Referees, Wager (lamports), Earned (lamports)\n- **Action column**: None; renders user as Link to `/users/{userId}` for drill-down\n- **Actor role prop**: None today\n\n**DogpileEventsTable**\n- **Props**: `{ rows: ReadonlyArray<PeekDogpileEventRow>; error?: string | null }`\n- **Columns**: Status (StatusChip), Campaign, Starts, Ends, Multiplier, Game entries, Point grants, Created, ID\n- **Action column**: None\n- **Actor role prop**: None today\n\n**FraudFlagsTable**\n- **Props**: `{ rows: ReadonlyArray<PeekFraudFlagListRow>; error?: string | null }`\n- **Columns**: Status (StatusChip), Flag type, User, Wallet, Related, Details (JSON), Created, Resolved, ID\n- **Action column**: None; User renders as Link to `/users/{userId}`\n- **Actor role prop**: None today\n\n**RewardConfigTable**\n- **Props**: `{ rows: ReadonlyArray<PeekRewardConfigRow>; error?: string | null }`\n- **Columns**: Key, Type (StatusChip), Value, Definition, Updated\n- **Action column**: None\n- **Actor role prop**: None today\n\n### 4. Access Policy Details\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/server/access-policy.ts`\n\n**PEEK_ACTION_RULES** (lines 154-159):\n```\nkol_rate.update → [\"business\", \"admin\"]\nfraud_flag.status.update → [\"admin\"]\ndogpile.cancel → [\"admin\"]\nreward_config.update → [\"admin\"]\n```\n\n**getPeekActorContext() shape** (lines 22-25, 115-125):\n```\n{ email: string; role: PeekRole }\nwhere PeekRole = \"business\" | \"admin\"\n```\n\n**Exported helper**: `isActionAllowedForRole(actionId, role, rules?)` (lines 209-218) — returns boolean; fails closed for unknown action ids.\n\n### 5. Server Actions Pattern\n\n**Finding**: No `\"use server\"` directives found anywhere in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src`. The codebase does **not yet use Next.js Server Actions**.\n\n**Mutation infrastructure exists as standalone functions** (engine-only modules in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/server/mutations/`) that can be imported and called from route handlers or Server Actions. The `runPeekMutation` orchestrator (in `runner.ts`) handles auth, validation, transaction wrapping, and audit logging.\n\n### 6. Component Test Framework & Pattern\n\n**Test file naming**: `{ComponentName}.test.tsx` (e.g., `fraud-flags-table.test.tsx`, `growth-kol-table.test.tsx`, `dogpile-events-table.test.tsx`, `reward-config-table.test.tsx`)\n\n**Framework & utilities**:\n- **Test runner**: Vitest (`vitest` 3.2.4)\n- **DOM testing**: `@testing-library/react` (16.3.2)\n- **Setup utilities**: `@testing-library/jest-dom` (6.9.1), `jsdom` (24.1.3)\n- **Test discovery**: Vitest auto-discovers `.test.tsx` files\n\n### 7. Package Scripts\n\n```json\n{\n  \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n  \"test:watch\": \"vitest\",\n  \"lint\": \"eslint .\",\n  \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit -p tsconfig.typecheck.json\",\n  \"verify\": \"pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck && pnpm test && pnpm build\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n**Summary**: All four pages are set up with role gating via `getPeekActorContext()` and `isRouteAllowedForRole()`. The mutations are engine-only (no Server Actions yet) and fully unit-tested. Tables are read-only with no action columns; wiring will require adding \"use server\" route handlers (or actions) to invoke `runPeekMutation` and adding action buttons/dialogs to the four tables. Test pattern is clear: vitest + @testing-library/react."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3fc3c40b-0944-44dd-9202-74a9cef80e25","uui